<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="479" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="201.[1988,2581,1714,2137]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">
Taxonomy of A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" box="[2247,2297,1828,1861]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="toba">toba</taxonomicName>
is poorly resolved. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="479" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707542" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707542/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" targetBox="[1373,1965,1713,2126]" targetPageId="201">
<paragraph blockId="201.[1988,2581,1714,2137]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1988,2164,1907,1940]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">Distribution.</emphasis>
SE Bolivia, W Paraguay, extreme SW Brazil, and N 
<taxonomicName box="[2327,2471,1950,1979]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="479" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="201.[1988,2581,1714,2137]" lastBlockId="201.[1373,2580,2147,2727]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1988,2273,1990,2019]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 91-126 mm, tail 67-85 mm, ear 16-20 mm, hindfoot 24-27 mm; weight 25-57 g. The 
<taxonomicName authority="Grass Mouse" authorityName="Grass Mouse" box="[1988,2255,2104,2137]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Toba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Toba Grass Mouse</taxonomicName>
is a moderately large species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1528,1627,2147,2176]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is olivaceous, finely ticked with gray; eye-ring is present but not clearly defined; venteris frosted grayish, white, or buffy; some specimens have white spot on chin; and tail is sharply bicolored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="479" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="201.[1373,2580,2147,2727]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1375,1486,2261,2294]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">Habitat.</emphasis>
Chacoan ecoregion, including grassland, patches of forest intermingled with palm savanna, marshland, thorn forest, semiarid scrublands, and gallery forest, at elevations below 1000 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1375,1875,2378,2411]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="201.[1373,2580,2147,2727]" box="[1375,1875,2378,2411]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1375,1636,2378,2411]" pageId="201" pageNumber="479">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
